constraints_details.result: Hinterland Lower Lea Valley including Stratford

description: Demolition of Tweed House and associated buildings (including the lowering in height of the adjacent towpath wall) and the erection of a new building ranging in 6 to 13 storeys in height to provide 115 new residential units (including 33 x 1 bed, 43 x 2 bed, 31 x 3 bed, 7 x 4 bed and 1 x 5 bed), with associated disabled parking, cycle parking facilities, landscaped open space and private amenity space.
